main event: Radar detected an unidentified object in Plainview, New York on July 31, 1951, with both ground and airborne radar confirming its presence.
interesting points: The observation lasted several minutes and involved an object described as intermittent and possibly hovering., The exact nature and identity of the object could not be determined from the collected data., More investigation is recommended to understand the radar target., Witnesses included the radar operators who confirmed the Object's presence., The report mentions a potential connection to Project Blue Book's investigations.
witness description: radar operators and observers involved in the project
